President Joe Biden met with Ukraine's Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba to emphasize the United States' commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. Biden informed Kuleba about the US response to Russia's recognition of the self-proclaimed "independence" of the DNR and LNR regions in Ukraine, including the recent Executive Order and sanctions. Biden also reassured Kuleba that the US would continue to provide security assistance and macroeconomic support to Ukraine. Additionally, Biden reiterated the United States' readiness to swiftly and decisively respond to any further Russian aggression against Ukraine, in collaboration with allies and partners.